[assistant] Fixed the `invalid constant type: 18` failure and amended the commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Cause:
[assistant] - `javassist:3.12.0.GA` cannot parse modern test bytecode containing newer constant-pool entries.
[assistant] - The exported fixture was previously compiled from `src/test/java`, so `StubGenerator.makeProxyClass(...)` tried to parse modern bytecode and failed.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change:
[assistant] - Replaced the exported source fixture with a small precompiled Java 8 bytecode fixture:
[assistant]   - `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/bytecode/javassist_javassist/AppletServerRmiFixture.class`
[assistant] - Updated `AppletServerTest` to export that fixture instead.
[assistant] - The RMI request now passes a `RemoteRef`, so `AppletServer.readParameters(...)` still reaches `ObjectInputStream#readObject()` and resolves the remote reference back to the exported object.
[assistant] - The successful boolean response still reaches `ObjectOutputStream#writeObject(...)`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Amended commit:
[assistant] - `503dad2a67 Add AppletServer RMI coverage for javassist`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests. The untracked metadata file remains untouched.
[assistant-event] text_end
